POLICE have launched an investigation after a woman was allegedly shot and killed, while her infant was left unharmed, in Laezonia in Tshwane. Despite the incident happening on 27 May 2022, the police are still looking for the suspect behind the gruesome murder. According to Gauteng police spokesman Lieutenant Colonel Mavela Masondo, the police are still searching for the suspect. He said the body of a woman with gunshot wounds was found in Laezonia and next to the deceased was a baby, who was left unharmed. ALSO READ: Newborn baby found abandoned behind a transformer! “Community members reported that they heard gunshots, which were followed by baby cries, and it triggered them to investigate what was happening. They made a gruesome discovery of the body of a woman and a baby laying next to her in the bushes. Police and Emergency Services were immediately called to the scene and the woman in her late 20s was certified dead. The infant was taken to a place of safety,” he said. Masondo said a case of murder was opened at Erasmia Police Station for further police investigation. “Police are appealing to anyone who might have information that can help in the investigation and assist to locate the family of the deceased to please call the investigating officer, Sergeant Lawrence Phaahla on 072 766 0088 or 012 370 1074/5,” said Masondo.